Here is one way to change the font for the h1 element:

```css
h1 {
  /* Set the font family */
  font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
}
```

In the example above, the font family is set to the Arial font, with Helvetica and sans-serif as fallback options. You can put any font of your choice.

Here is a simple Java program that will output the message "Hello World!":

```java
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello World!");
    }
}
```

To run this program, you will need to have the Java Development Kit (JDK) installed on your computer. Once the JDK is installed, you can open a command prompt or terminal, navigate to the directory where you saved the above code, and run the following commands:

```
javac HelloWorld.java
java HelloWorld
```

The first command (`javac`) compiles the Java code into bytecode, which can be executed by the Java Virtual Machine (JVM). The second command (`java`) runs the program, causing the message "Hello World!" to be printed to the screen.
